div2.p:
Matter is composed of earth; Mind of God's eternal breath. Matter yields to form and word;
                            Mind alone, can worship God. Mind is master of the man. Matter, servant of his plan. Mind
                            retains its vigor long, Matter fails e'er mind is strong. Mind can scale the Universe ;
                            Matter, law confines, to earth. Mind retains its vernal bloom When matter lieth in the tomb.
                            Canterbury, N. H.

div3.p:
Dyspepsia is cured by muscular exercise, voluntary or involuntary, and cannot be cured
                               in any other way, because nothing can create or collect gastric juice except exercise;
                               it is a product of the human machine. Nature only can make it.
